pageTitle: 20th annual car show at Ayers center | ChieflandCitizen.com
TableContextTimeStampAfterTable: {36358=Copyright © 2015, 27378=   The Early Ford V-8 Club of America Suwannee River Region No. 140 will celebrate its 20th anniversary  of sponsoring the Annual Antique Car Show at Ayers Health and Rehabilitation Center on Saturday from 10 a.m. to 2 p.m.    The show is for cars from 1987 and earlier. Dash plaques, Best of Show and People's Choice awards to the Top 20 cars will be awarded. Judging will be by participants in the show.  The registration fee to show a car is $15 per vehicle. All proceeds will be donated to charity and admission to the event is free.    For more information, call Myrna Williams at 352-463-2365.}
